wfAotDelete.name: wfAotDelete
wfAotDelete.description: Create/Delete parameter. Default is created. User perform an SNMP SET operation on this object in order to create/delete AOT

wfAotDisable.name: wfAotDisable
wfAotDisable.description: Enable/Disable parameter. Default is enabled. User perform an SNMP SET operation on this object in order to enable/disable AOT

wfAotInterfaceTable.name: wfAotInterfaceTable
wfAotInterfaceTable.description: Interface table which lists all PASYNC line entries and other line related information

wfAotInterfaceDelete.name: wfAotInterfaceDelete
wfAotInterfaceDelete.description: Create/Delete attribute. Default is Created Users perform SNMP SET operation on this object in order to create/delete a translation interface record

wfAotInterfaceDisable.name: wfAotInterfaceDisable
wfAotInterfaceDisable.description: Enables/Disables this mapping entry Setting of this attribute to DISABLED will disconnect all active sessions pertaining to this interface entry

wfAotInterfaceCctNumber.name: wfAotInterfaceCctNumber
wfAotInterfaceCctNumber.description: The circuit from which the connection attempt is received that initiates a translation session.

wfAotInterfaceSlotNumber.name: wfAotInterfaceSlotNumber
wfAotInterfaceSlotNumber.description: Slot number on which this interface is running

wfAotInterfaceState.name: wfAotInterfaceState
wfAotInterfaceState.description: The current state of the Interface

wfAotInterfaceType.name: wfAotInterfaceType
wfAotInterfaceType.description: If this interface is point-to-point, i.e. no splitting occurs we can straight away deliver PASC frame to designated TCP circuit

wfAotInterfaceAttachedTo.name: wfAotInterfaceAttachedTo
wfAotInterfaceAttachedTo.description: Information that this interface is attached to the Primary or secondary PASC station

wfAotKeepaliveInterval.name: wfAotKeepaliveInterval
wfAotKeepaliveInterval.description: Idle session timeout period, in seconds. If an established TCP connection remains inactive for this interval, KEEPALIVE messages will be sent to the peer (if the Keepalive Timer is non-zero). Setting the Idle Timer to zero disables the keepalive feature.

wfAotKeepaliveRto.name: wfAotKeepaliveRto
wfAotKeepaliveRto.description: KEEPALIVE retransmit timeout period, in seconds. This is the interval at which unacknowledged KEEPALIVE messages will be retransmitted. If the Idle Timer is set to zero, this timer ignored. If the Idle Timer is non-zero and this timer IS zero, no KEEPALIVEs are sent and the session is terminated upon expiration of the Idle Timer.

wfAotKeepaliveMaxRetry.name: wfAotKeepaliveMaxRetry
wfAotKeepaliveMaxRetry.description: Number of unacknowledged KEEPALIVE messages retransmitted before the TCP session is terminated. If this count is set to zero, only one KEEPALIVE message will be sent.

wfAotPeerTable.name: wfAotPeerTable
wfAotPeerTable.description: Peer table lists all TCP connections this router will have with its peers

wfAotPeerEntryDelete.name: wfAotPeerEntryDelete
wfAotPeerEntryDelete.description: Create/Delete attribute. Default is Created Users perform SNMP SET operation on this object in order to create/delete a peer record

wfAotPeerEntryDisable.name: wfAotPeerEntryDisable
wfAotPeerEntryDisable.description: Enables/Disables this mapping entry Setting of this attribute to DISABLED will disconnect all active sessions pertaining to this interface entry

wfAotPeerSlotNumber.name: wfAotPeerSlotNumber
wfAotPeerSlotNumber.description: Slot number on which this peer entry is configured

wfAotPeerCctNumber.name: wfAotPeerCctNumber
wfAotPeerCctNumber.description: The circuit from which the connection attempt is received that initiates a translation session.

wfAotPeerRemoteIpAddr.name: wfAotPeerRemoteIpAddr
wfAotPeerRemoteIpAddr.description: IP Address of the remote host with which this translation session is established.

wfAotConnOriginator.name: wfAotConnOriginator
wfAotConnOriginator.description: Upon start up, based on the configuration either partner is going to initiate TCP conn. or myself

wfAotPeerLocalTcpListenPort.name: wfAotPeerLocalTcpListenPort
wfAotPeerLocalTcpListenPort.description: Based on the field wfAotConnOriginator, SiteManager will allow user to configure only one of following two fields: if Originator = SELF then through SiteManager ask user to enter PeerTcpListenPort# else through SiteManager ask user to enter LocalTcpListenPort# So, in any case one of the two fields will have NULL_VALUE.

wfAotPeerRemoteTcpListenPort.name: wfAotPeerRemoteTcpListenPort
wfAotPeerRemoteTcpListenPort.description: Peer listen port for TCP connection

wfAotPeerLocalTcpPort.name: wfAotPeerLocalTcpPort
wfAotPeerLocalTcpPort.description: When TCP connection is established, we will have other TCP port number available which is assigned by the system from the available pool. We will fill in this information here in this READ_ONLY variable. Again, based on Originator only one of the following two fields will have valid value. if Originator = SELF then fill in LocalTcpPort field inside the AOT module else fill in PeerTcpPort field inside the AOT module In short, ========= For Originator = SELF PeerTcpListenPort and LocalTcpPort entries are valid For Originator = PARTNER LocalTcpListenPort and PeerTcpPort entries are valid

wfAotPeerRemoteTcpPort.name: wfAotPeerRemoteTcpPort
wfAotPeerRemoteTcpPort.description: Peer TCP port of the connection
